{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"710f1db3-8f82-4482-9ae7-7d1ae6f5d748","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. **Optionally** enable the new test app entry point:\n   ```xml\n   <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes your test project a standalone app).\n\nThat's the core migration. The new runner is faster and supports parallel execution at the assembly level out of the box. Your existing `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` tests require no changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"61e1371a-4e82-4a86-b520-35aa352b07b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"BD0D:2DE6FB:1CE0FBF:208CEA8:6A07C429"},"id":"c8043a69-d43c-499c-b776-8d4eef766270","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:11:15.046Z","parentId":"41f71216-d8c5-43d6-9fd5-d6378d8890a1"}
